  "ciliary_role": "Also calles CAP350. Facilitates the localization of CEP19 to the centriole (28659385). CEP250 is necessary for recruitment of FOP and provides a docking site for it at the centrosome. Both CEP250 and FOP form a complex and are required for  anchoring to the centrosome (16314388). CEP350-FOP complex promotes recruitment of both the CEP19-RABL2B complex and TTBK2 to the mother centriole (28625565). Centriole growth is regulated by CAP350, which is also required early during the procentriole assembly process when the first microtubule is polymerised (19052644)",
